article.headline: Rhode Island 29, Northeastern 14
article.story: BROOKLINE, Mass. -- Jimmy Hughes and Anthony Ferrer combined for 164 rushing yards and two touchdowns as Rhode Island defeated Northeastern 29-14 on Saturday. Hughes rushed for 93 yards on 21 carries for Rhode Island (3-9, 1-7 Colonial Athletic Association), scoring on an 11-yard run early in the second half. Ferrer rushed 10 times for 71 yards and scored on a 3-yard TD run with just over two minutes remaining in the game. John Griffin scored two touchdowns and had 110 yards rushing on 18 carries for Northeastern (2-10, 1-7 CAA). Rhode Island's Derek Cassidy was 13-of-22 for 157 passing yards, while kicker Louis Feinstein had three field goals. Northeastern's Anthony Orio was just 5-of-17 for 47 yards and an interception. Northeastern led 14-13 at halftime.
